resources.string: Our mission is to contribute to the common good by lighting the path to wisdom and empowering women and men to pursue meaningful lives as productive, responsible citizens.\n\nInspired by a shared commitment to excellence and the desire to transcend traditional higher-education boundaries, SUNY Oswego will be a premier institution that provides a transformative experience to a diverse body of students, empowering them to live ethical and meaningful lives and build a better world.

Brandon Agostinelli is currently a junior computer science major at Oswego State.

His interest in computers began after his freshmen year at Oswego State. And since then, being the motivated learner that his is, his goal from the start has been to learn how machines and systems work both inside software and hardware.

Brandon joined the development team for this application in late August 2014. He graduated from Penfield High School in Rochester New York in 2012.

Home is of the upmost importance to him in more ways than one. Brandon is set to graduate in the spring of 2016. His favorite all time thing is Baseball, just as him. Brandon spends loads of his time when not working on projects and other assignments on enjoying the outdoors and playing sports with friends and family. He can be contacted at bagostin (at) oswego (dot) edu.
